- `README`

## Existing build notes visible in the repo

The existing repository README says to build `muParserx` first, then adjust Qwt include and library paths inside `QwtControl.pro`, then run `qmake` and `make`.

## Likely build flow

```bash
cd muparserx_v2_1_6
make
cd ..
qmake
make
```

You may need to edit `QwtControl.pro` to match your local Qwt include and linker paths.

## What this project appears to do

This is partly inferred from the repository structure, but likely areas include:
- plotting and graphing using Qwt,
- modeling continuous and discrete systems,
- inverse Laplace and numeric methods,
- equation handling and function parsing,
- educational or exploratory control-engineering workflows.

## What a stronger README should explain

- main user workflows,
- supported Qt and Qwt versions,
- whether the app still builds on modern Linux systems,
- bundled versus external dependencies,
- screenshots and example sessions.

## Caveats

The repository looks older and may require manual path editing and older qmake/Qwt assumptions.

